WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:04.004
Adult Adam: <i>Back in the '80s,</i>
<i>the greatest frat comedy</i>

00:04.004 --> 00:06.215
<i>of them all was</i>
<i>"Animal House"...</i>
Food fight!

00:06.215 --> 00:08.550
<i>...the story of a group of</i>
<i>weirdos and underdogs</i>

00:08.550 --> 00:10.928
<i>who overcame all obstacles</i>
<i>to rule the school.</i>

00:10.928 --> 00:12.679
<i>And with Barry</i>
<i>finally in college,</i>

00:12.679 --> 00:15.807
<i>he wasted no time</i>
<i>living out his favorite movie.</i>

00:15.807 --> 00:16.892
I'm joining
a fraternity.

00:16.892 --> 00:18.185
Ugh. Why?

00:18.185 --> 00:20.771
Bros, babes, beer,
and boat shoes!

00:20.771 --> 00:23.357
Classism, hazing, dangerously
excessive drinking.

00:23.357 --> 00:25.234
Yeah, all of those
awesome reasons.

00:25.234 --> 00:27.236
Okay,
horseshoe menorahs.

00:27.236 --> 00:28.403
Wow me.

00:28.403 --> 00:30.280
We're Omega Psi.
It's the Greek alphabet.

00:30.280 --> 00:31.490
Is that not clear?

00:31.490 --> 00:33.492
He struggles with
the English alphabet, so...

00:33.492 --> 00:35.327
If I were to pledge,
could I expect

00:35.327 --> 00:36.578
the following hijinks ‐‐

00:36.578 --> 00:38.789
driving a motorcycle
into a crowded party,

00:38.789 --> 00:40.415
leaving a dead horse
in a dean's office,

00:40.415 --> 00:42.292
and/or road‐tripping
to an all‐girls college

00:42.292 --> 00:44.211
to hit on the friends of
a deceased student?

00:44.211 --> 00:45.754
We're more
of an academic house.

00:45.754 --> 00:46.755
Next!

00:46.755 --> 00:48.006
Hey. Erik Stratton,

00:48.006 --> 00:49.341
alumni director
at Delta House.

00:49.341 --> 00:50.425
Damn glad to meet ya.

00:50.425 --> 00:52.427
That was Erik Stratton,
alumni director.

00:52.427 --> 00:53.595
He was damn glad
to meet you.
[ Chuckles ]

00:53.595 --> 00:55.931
Why are you talking to me?
I already have a grandpa.

00:55.931 --> 00:57.266
Oh, we're doing the recruiting
'cause most of the guys

00:57.266 --> 00:59.101
in our frat are
either hungover or...

00:59.101 --> 01:00.352
In jail.
...in jail.

01:00.352 --> 01:01.937
Oh, I don't <i>not</i> like
what I'm hearing.

01:01.937 --> 01:03.689
Cold one?
It's 9:00 in the morning.

01:03.689 --> 01:04.982
Yeah,
we got a late start.

01:04.982 --> 01:05.983
Let me ask you
something.

01:05.983 --> 01:08.110
Can your house serve my needs

01:08.110 --> 01:09.736
as an alpha male
in the upper echelons

01:09.736 --> 01:11.280
of society's
wealthy and elite?

01:11.280 --> 01:13.615
Ha! Not even a little.
Let me ask <i>you</i> something.

01:13.615 --> 01:15.075
Is that a Froot Loop
in your hair?

01:15.075 --> 01:16.451
It's an Apple Jack.

01:16.451 --> 01:19.371
This conversation
is over.

01:19.371 --> 01:20.664
So, how many pledges
do we have now?

01:20.664 --> 01:21.790
None yet.

01:21.790 --> 01:23.166
Oh. One more,
and we got one.

01:23.166 --> 01:24.501
Barry, I don't care
what you do,

01:24.501 --> 01:26.378
but don't you think you're
being a tad unrealistic

01:26.378 --> 01:28.338
about which fraternity
is the right one for you?

01:28.338 --> 01:29.756
Silence!

01:29.756 --> 01:31.883
I've found my people.

01:31.883 --> 01:33.552
<i>Yep, they were</i>
<i>the perfect‐haired,</i>

01:33.552 --> 01:35.762
<i>pastel‐wearing blowhards</i>
<i>of Beta Zeta,</i>

01:35.762 --> 01:37.681
<i>and Barry</i>
<i>had to be one of them.</i>

01:37.681 --> 01:39.391
Those khaki Ken Dolls?

01:39.391 --> 01:40.350
You're kidding, right?

01:40.350 --> 01:42.019
Hi. Barry Goldberg.

01:42.019 --> 01:44.730
And, no, you are not looking
into a mirror.

01:44.730 --> 01:46.064
What can I do for you?

01:46.064 --> 01:48.608
Well, it's obvious
I'm Beta Zeta material,

01:48.608 --> 01:50.652
so why don't you just
make me a brother now

01:50.652 --> 01:52.779
so we can start making morally
questionable choices together?

01:52.779 --> 01:54.531
Barry, I'm leaving.

01:54.531 --> 01:56.491
All the smirking and popped
collars are wigging me out.

01:56.491 --> 01:58.660
Okay, girl I've never met.

01:58.660 --> 02:00.704
Hi. I'm Beta Zeta president
Rick Kentwood.

02:00.704 --> 02:01.830
Of course you are.

02:01.830 --> 02:02.998
And if you're not busy
tomorrow night,

02:02.998 --> 02:04.166
you should come by
our house.

02:04.166 --> 02:05.876
We're hosting
a classy get‐together.

02:05.876 --> 02:07.044
"The Get Trashed Bash"?

02:07.044 --> 02:08.545
Was "Douche Gala" taken?

02:08.545 --> 02:09.755
We accept!

02:09.755 --> 02:12.049
Me and this mouthy lady stranger
will be there.

02:12.049 --> 02:13.300
What are you doing?

02:13.300 --> 02:14.676
There's no way
I'm going to that.

02:14.676 --> 02:16.219
You have to!

02:16.219 --> 02:18.972
For some unknown reason,
he's taken with you.

02:18.972 --> 02:22.267
So, we go, I charm him,
ditch you,

02:22.267 --> 02:24.770
and my life of nonstop
toga adventures begins.

02:24.770 --> 02:26.271
I guess that would mean
that you'd have to move

02:26.271 --> 02:28.023
out of our dorm and I'd never
see your dumb face again.

02:28.023 --> 02:29.399
We see it the same way.

02:29.399 --> 02:32.444
Now time to practice my lovable
frat‐brother antics,

02:32.444 --> 02:34.196
like crushing beer cans
against my forehead.

02:35.155 --> 02:37.324
I know your weak spot,
Mr. Pibb!

02:37.324 --> 02:39.368
[ Groans ]
I'm softening it up.

02:39.368 --> 02:40.869
[ Crunch ]
Aah!

02:40.869 --> 02:42.371
♪ I'm twisted up inside ♪

02:42.371 --> 02:45.874
♪ But nonetheless,
I feel the need to say ♪

02:48.251 --> 02:49.711
♪ I don't know the future ♪

02:49.711 --> 02:53.298
♪ But the past keeps getting
clearer every day ♪

02:53.298 --> 02:56.009
<i>It was October 16th,</i>
<i>1980‐something,</i>

02:56.009 --> 02:57.928
<i>and my mom was still adjusting</i>
<i>to the fact</i>

02:57.928 --> 02:59.971
<i>that there was only one kid</i>
<i>in the house to cook for.</i>

02:59.971 --> 03:01.181
Adam, breakfast!

03:02.432 --> 03:05.185
Uh, I already had
some Mr. T cereal.

03:05.185 --> 03:06.812
Well [As Mr. T]
I pity the fool

03:06.812 --> 03:08.939
who doesn't eat
my pigs in a blanket.

03:08.939 --> 03:10.941
Again
you made too much.

03:10.941 --> 03:12.984
Your two other kids
are off in college.

03:12.984 --> 03:14.903
How do you not know
that by now?

03:14.903 --> 03:16.488
Oh, I'm just
fueling Adam up

03:16.488 --> 03:18.365
with high‐energy meats
for our big day.

03:18.365 --> 03:20.450
Big day?
With me? And also you?

03:20.450 --> 03:22.202
Surprise!
It's robot‐themed.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.412
Robots?

03:23.412 --> 03:25.330
Adam, she knows
your greatest weakness.

03:25.330 --> 03:27.124
We start off
by going to a matinee

03:27.124 --> 03:29.126
of this new movie
called "The Terminator"

03:29.126 --> 03:31.336
and then we move
to Kiddie City

03:31.336 --> 03:33.630
to pick up the Transformer toy
of your choice

03:33.630 --> 03:34.881
and, for the finale,

03:34.881 --> 03:36.925
we're gonna see Styx
at the Spectrum

03:36.925 --> 03:38.718
perform "Mr. Roboto."

03:38.718 --> 03:40.554
While I appreciate
the pandering,

03:40.554 --> 03:42.556
I'm afraid I already have plans
with Dave Kim.

03:42.556 --> 03:43.849
Dave Kim?

03:43.849 --> 03:45.767
You're gonna blow off a day
with me and robots

03:45.767 --> 03:47.894
for that four‐eyed drip?

03:47.894 --> 03:49.563
Yeah.
We were just gonna hang,

03:49.563 --> 03:52.065
but now I think we're gonna do
all your robot stuff instead.

03:52.065 --> 03:54.067
Thanks for the idea!

03:54.067 --> 03:56.820
Beverly, enough with
overwhelming Adam

03:56.820 --> 03:58.113
with all your love.

03:58.113 --> 04:00.073
You need to find
someone else.

04:00.073 --> 04:00.991
Well, what have
you got cooking today?

04:00.991 --> 04:02.617
You wanna see
some robots?

04:02.617 --> 04:04.119
I'm pretty jammed up,

04:04.119 --> 04:07.122
but I know who you should ask ‐‐
your life partner.

04:07.122 --> 04:08.665
You just saw Adam leave.

04:08.665 --> 04:10.792
I'm talking about Murray!

04:10.792 --> 04:12.711
Yeah. Murray's good
at a lot of things,

04:12.711 --> 04:14.838
but doing stuff
isn't one of them.

04:14.838 --> 04:18.216
You used to go to movies,
weekends down the shore.

04:18.216 --> 04:21.386
Go back to that magical time
before you had kids

04:21.386 --> 04:23.138
and start living!

04:23.138 --> 04:24.347
[ Grumbles ]

04:24.347 --> 04:25.807
[ Whispering ]
Now's your chance.

04:25.807 --> 04:28.018
<i>In that moment, my mom realized</i>

04:28.018 --> 04:30.937
<i>she had to get Murray out of</i>
<i>his chair and into her life.</i>

04:30.937 --> 04:32.647
<i>It wasn't going to be easy.</i>

04:32.647 --> 04:33.940
[ Grumbles, sighs ]

04:33.940 --> 04:35.025
Is that you saying
"Good morning"?

04:35.025 --> 04:36.485
[ Grumbles ]

04:36.485 --> 04:38.653
<i>As my mom worried</i>
<i>about her future,</i>

04:38.653 --> 04:41.865
<i>my bro gathered his oldest pals</i>
<i>for an important powwow.</i>

04:41.865 --> 04:44.326
Thanks for coming to the weekly
meeting of the JTP.

04:44.326 --> 04:45.660
All: JTP!

04:45.660 --> 04:46.912
First order
of business ‐‐

04:46.912 --> 04:48.663
it's almost Matt Bradley's
birthday, and I ‐‐

04:48.663 --> 04:50.665
No one cares about stupid
Matt Bradley

04:50.665 --> 04:52.876
and how embarrassingly old
he's getting.

04:52.876 --> 04:55.253
It's true. No one likes to be
confronted by their mortality.

04:55.253 --> 04:56.838
Let's not make a big deal
about it.

04:56.838 --> 04:59.841
We won't. First non‐boring item
to discuss ‐‐

04:59.841 --> 05:03.011
Big Tasty will be leaving
shortly to attend a frat party.

05:03.011 --> 05:04.513
‐Good for you.
‐Fun.

05:04.513 --> 05:06.723
Greek life!
Sorry my birthday
almost got in the way.

05:06.723 --> 05:09.559
And I will likely be joining
their brotherhood as a pledge.

05:09.559 --> 05:10.977
You're killing it
in college!

05:10.977 --> 05:12.646
And you're not the only one

05:12.646 --> 05:15.023
'cause I just made
Haverford's varsity crew team

05:15.023 --> 05:16.608
as their coxswain.

05:16.608 --> 05:19.486
And everyone over at Villanova
is loving my nakedness.

05:19.486 --> 05:21.613
It's really nice to be a part
of an open‐minded community

05:21.613 --> 05:23.031
where nudity is celebrated.

05:23.031 --> 05:25.617
My gap year working at The Gap
couldn't be going better.

05:25.617 --> 05:28.411
I'm getting paid, and I'm
learning a valuable jean‐craft.

05:28.411 --> 05:30.413
And I just took my immersion
into the Grateful Dead culture

05:30.413 --> 05:31.581
to the next level.

05:31.581 --> 05:33.375
Look.
I grew my first dreadlock.

05:33.375 --> 05:36.002
Look at us absolutely destroy
post‐high school, JTP.

05:36.002 --> 05:37.212
All: JTP!

05:37.212 --> 05:38.839
That's why when I'm a frat god

05:38.839 --> 05:40.465
and I ignore you
and treat you like crap,

05:40.465 --> 05:41.716
I won't feel that bad.

05:41.716 --> 05:43.718
[ Laughs ] JTP.

05:43.718 --> 05:45.762
All: JTP?

05:45.762 --> 05:48.014
<i>While Barry left his crew</i>
<i>in the dust for Greek life,</i>

05:48.014 --> 05:50.725
<i>my mom was on a mission to get</i>
<i>my dad to</i> enjoy <i>life.</i>

05:50.725 --> 05:53.603
Come on! Get up! It's just
a harmless head injury.

05:53.603 --> 05:56.523
God did not intend the human
neck to bend that way.

05:56.523 --> 05:58.191
Man, I love football.

05:58.191 --> 05:59.985
‐For sure.
‐It's all I have.

05:59.985 --> 06:02.112
Murray, I'm gonna need
five minutes of your time

06:02.112 --> 06:03.613
and also the rest
of your life.

06:03.613 --> 06:05.240
What is this? I'm in the middle
of a game here.

06:05.240 --> 06:07.367
You are aware
that in two years,

06:07.367 --> 06:09.369
all of our little angels
will be out of the house.

06:09.369 --> 06:11.872
Just the thought of it
makes me smile. Watch.

06:13.331 --> 06:15.584
Oh, no. I've never seen
your face do that.

06:15.584 --> 06:17.627
You can tell the skin doesn't
even know how to crease.

06:17.627 --> 06:20.213
Well, unlike you, I live
in total terror of that day

06:20.213 --> 06:22.382
and all the sad and lonely ones
that will follow.

06:22.382 --> 06:25.468
Been there. After Lainey left,
things got dark.

06:25.468 --> 06:29.097
I rarely ate, showered,
or ventured outside.

06:29.097 --> 06:30.640
My hollow shell of a body

06:30.640 --> 06:33.643
would crawl out of Lainey's
tear‐stained bedroom

06:33.643 --> 06:36.021
only to answer a phone
that wasn't ringing.

06:36.021 --> 06:37.731
Is this why
you didn't bring the nachos?

06:37.731 --> 06:38.982
Yeah.

06:38.982 --> 06:40.692
Bevy, all kids
leave at some point.

06:40.692 --> 06:41.776
What do you want me to do?

06:41.776 --> 06:43.486
To reconnect with me.

06:43.486 --> 06:46.364
Let's pick out some activities
we can do together

06:46.364 --> 06:48.700
to help fill the terrible void
of their departure.

06:48.700 --> 06:49.701
Activities?

06:49.701 --> 06:51.161
Golf.
Too much walking.

06:51.161 --> 06:52.454
Putt‐putt golf.
Too much walking.

06:52.454 --> 06:54.205
Crocheting?
My fingers are too thick,

06:54.205 --> 06:55.582
and also
I don't want to.

06:55.582 --> 06:58.293
You just rattle them off.
I'll tell you when you hit one.

06:58.293 --> 06:59.419
Wine tasting.

06:59.419 --> 07:00.712
Cooking class.
Bowling.

07:00.712 --> 07:02.213
Sightseeing.
Bird watching.

07:02.213 --> 07:03.882
Learning a new language.
Ceramics.

07:03.882 --> 07:06.009
‐Yeah!
‐Ceramics it is!

07:06.009 --> 07:07.594
No, no, no. The Eagles
finally got a first down.

07:07.594 --> 07:08.762
I'm not doing pottery.

07:08.762 --> 07:10.597
Damn it, Murray,
stop being such a lump!

07:10.597 --> 07:12.932
This is the rest of our lives
we're talking about!

07:12.932 --> 07:14.434
Hey, you're complaining
about things.

07:14.434 --> 07:16.019
I'm listening.
We're doing stuff.

07:16.019 --> 07:17.687
That's not what I meant,
and you know it.

07:20.357 --> 07:22.901
Don't worry, Bev.
Murray's a good guy.

07:22.901 --> 07:23.902
He'll come around.

07:23.902 --> 07:25.612
The best.
But also the worst.

07:25.612 --> 07:27.656
He once told me
I was too bald to look at.

07:27.656 --> 07:29.783
He didn't clarify and
I was too afraid to ask

07:29.783 --> 07:31.326
and now too much time
has passed.

07:31.326 --> 07:33.119
That is a deeply
upsetting story.

07:33.119 --> 07:34.704
For sure,
but I love the guy.

07:34.704 --> 07:38.208
And I do, too, but we all know
he's not gonna come around.

07:38.208 --> 07:39.250
[ Sighs ]

07:39.250 --> 07:41.419
If the past 20 years
have taught us anything,

07:41.419 --> 07:43.088
it's that he is gonna sit
in that damn chair

07:43.088 --> 07:44.464
for the rest of his life.

07:44.464 --> 07:45.757
No man can sit in a chair
for a lifetime.

07:45.757 --> 07:47.092
It can't be done.

07:47.092 --> 07:49.302
Agreed. Every man
has to move sometime.

07:49.302 --> 07:50.845
You don't believe me?

07:50.845 --> 07:52.514
Watch and learn.

07:52.514 --> 07:54.766
♪♪

07:54.766 --> 07:57.560
Meet me back here in six hours.

07:57.560 --> 07:59.938
<i>Yep, back before home</i>
<i>surveillance and nanny cams,</i>

07:59.938 --> 08:02.732
<i>my mom invented the Murray cam,</i>

08:02.732 --> 08:05.110
<i>and what she found</i>
<i>blew Bill and Vic's mind.</i>

08:05.110 --> 08:06.903
Unbelievable.

08:06.903 --> 08:09.781
If he didn't move that one time
to pet the dog,

08:09.781 --> 08:11.408
I'd swear
the VCR was paused.

08:11.408 --> 08:13.410
He's the most gifted sitter
I've ever seen.

08:13.410 --> 08:16.996
Maybe there is a way to get
Murray out of that chair.

08:16.996 --> 08:18.456
I'm gonna steal his friends.

08:18.456 --> 08:20.625
Oh, no!
He has other friends?!

08:20.625 --> 08:22.168
No. I'm talking about
you two dopes.

08:22.168 --> 08:23.420
Oh, good!

08:23.420 --> 08:25.755
If he sees us all
doing amazing things together,

08:25.755 --> 08:28.133
he's gonna get jealous
and want to do them, too.

08:28.133 --> 08:29.175
So, what are you saying,
Beverly?

08:29.175 --> 08:32.345
I'm saying come do
Tai Chi with me.

08:32.345 --> 08:33.471
Slo‐mo karate?

08:33.471 --> 08:35.306
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, that does sound fun.

08:35.306 --> 08:37.016
Well, I suppose
I've always wanted

08:37.016 --> 08:38.935
to be able
to tell people an anecdote.

08:38.935 --> 08:41.104
<i>While my mom's plan to join up</i>
<i>with my dad's best friends</i>

08:41.104 --> 08:42.439
<i>was in motion,</i>

08:42.439 --> 08:44.524
<i>Barry was going all out</i>
<i>to join Beta Zeta.</i>

08:44.524 --> 08:45.817
How do I look?

08:45.817 --> 08:48.361
Like a yacht captain
was run over by a polo horse.

08:48.361 --> 08:49.738
Perfect.

08:49.738 --> 08:51.406
There she is ‐‐

08:51.406 --> 08:52.991
the prettiest girl
on campus.

08:52.991 --> 08:57.328
And the prettiest boy.
[ Chuckles ]

08:57.328 --> 09:00.248
So, Erica, want to date
a future leader?

09:00.248 --> 09:02.459
I have a boyfriend,
and yuck.

09:02.459 --> 09:05.003
Well, watch me turn that yuck
into a yes.

09:05.003 --> 09:06.880
And watch me turn that yes
into a barf.

09:06.880 --> 09:08.715
Hi. Barry Goldberg.

09:08.715 --> 09:10.425
Frat nickname
to be determined,

09:10.425 --> 09:12.552
but I'm hoping to go with
"Captain Chug" or "Sexhawk."

09:12.552 --> 09:14.304
Excuse me.

09:14.304 --> 09:16.097
There you are!
Listen, Terry ‐‐

09:16.097 --> 09:16.890
It's Barry.

09:16.890 --> 09:18.308
That's hilarious.

09:18.308 --> 09:20.351
I want to introduce you
to some neat‐o guys

09:20.351 --> 09:21.770
that you
are going to love.

09:21.770 --> 09:23.271
Oh, sounds awesome, Rick.

09:24.606 --> 09:27.817
This is Leroy, Spock,
and Jimmy Flannigan.

09:27.817 --> 09:31.196
<i>Barry then realized</i>
<i>he was living "Animal House,"</i>

09:31.196 --> 09:32.864
<i>just not how he'd imagined.</i>

09:32.864 --> 09:34.157
I've been Floundered!

09:34.157 --> 09:35.283
What's "Floundered"?

09:35.283 --> 09:37.243
That husky loser
from "Animal House"

09:37.243 --> 09:39.746
who gets pawned off on a room
of a bunch of rejects.

09:39.746 --> 09:43.124
So what? This house is full of
cocky, entitled asswipes.

09:43.124 --> 09:44.751
And I hope to be them
someday,

09:44.751 --> 09:47.128
which is why I need to
turn this night around fast,

09:47.128 --> 09:48.713
and I know exactly how.

09:48.713 --> 09:50.548
I'm gonna pull a Bluto.

09:50.548 --> 09:52.008
Is that another
"Animal House" character?

09:52.008 --> 09:54.719
John Belushi's greatest role ‐‐
and now mine.

09:54.719 --> 09:56.763
‐♪ You know you make me wanna ♪
‐♪ Shout ♪

09:56.763 --> 09:59.015
♪ Kick my heels up and ♪
Food fight!

09:59.015 --> 10:01.684
<i>And with that,</i>
<i>Barry went full Bluto,</i>

10:01.684 --> 10:04.312
<i>plastered the frat‐house walls</i>
<i>with mashed potatoes.</i>

10:04.312 --> 10:07.148
<i>He totally destroyed</i>
<i>a complete stranger's guitar.</i>

10:07.148 --> 10:09.734
<i>He was, without a doubt,</i>
<i>the life of the party.</i>

10:09.734 --> 10:12.904
♪ A little bit softer now,
a little bit softer now ♪

10:12.904 --> 10:14.364
<i>Or so he thought.</i>

10:14.364 --> 10:15.865
♪ ...now,
a little bit softer now ♪

10:15.865 --> 10:17.325
♪ Hey‐ey‐ey ♪

10:17.325 --> 10:18.910
[ Chuckles ]
What did I do?

10:18.910 --> 10:20.453
We should talk.

10:20.453 --> 10:22.789
Yes. I'd be honored
to join your fraternity.

10:22.789 --> 10:25.708
Listen, being a Beta Zeta ‐‐
it's all about being the best.

10:25.708 --> 10:27.210
And...

10:27.210 --> 10:28.128
you're not.

10:32.132 --> 10:34.551
<i>After Barry blew his shot</i>
<i>at frat glory,</i>

10:34.551 --> 10:36.094
<i>he had no choice but to</i>
<i>report back to the JTP.</i>

10:36.094 --> 10:38.263
JTP...
All: JTP?

10:38.263 --> 10:40.181
...I've called this emergency
meeting to tell you

10:40.181 --> 10:42.892
I will not be
a painfully handsome frat god

10:42.892 --> 10:44.352
who is above the law.

10:44.352 --> 10:45.603
I'll merely be
painfully handsome.

10:45.603 --> 10:47.021
I'm sorry, Bar.

10:47.021 --> 10:48.857
Those idiots don't know
what they're missing.

10:48.857 --> 10:50.859
But what hurts even more is,
while I'm flailing,

10:50.859 --> 10:52.277
you guys are out there
crushing it.

10:52.277 --> 10:54.237
While that's incredibly petty
and mean,

10:54.237 --> 10:55.905
the truth is,
we're actually not.

10:55.905 --> 10:58.241
I lied before about being
the coxswain of the rowing team.

10:58.241 --> 10:59.742
I just like saying
"coxswain."

10:59.742 --> 11:00.827
Coxswain.

11:00.827 --> 11:02.495
Oh. That is fun.

11:02.495 --> 11:05.039
And I hate how everyone at
Villanova also gets naked.

11:05.039 --> 11:07.000
There's nothing special
about me anymore.

11:07.000 --> 11:08.668
Everyone in my life is coming
out of the woodwork,

11:08.668 --> 11:10.253
asking for jean jackets.

11:10.253 --> 11:12.547
And I'll admit it ‐‐
this dreadlock isn't real!

11:12.547 --> 11:14.257
I found it.
You don't want to know more.

11:14.257 --> 11:16.467
I don't get it.
W‐Why did you lie?

11:16.467 --> 11:17.594
We didn't want you to worry
about us

11:17.594 --> 11:18.845
while you were having
the time of your life

11:18.845 --> 11:20.096
as a frat guy.

11:20.096 --> 11:21.848
But pledging
was a disaster.

11:21.848 --> 11:23.725
I tried everything
to impress them.

11:23.725 --> 11:26.060
I destroyed a guitar.
I threw food.

11:26.060 --> 11:29.314
I rolled on the ground.
What are these guys looking for?

11:29.314 --> 11:30.732
Forget about those
stupid frat guys.

11:30.732 --> 11:32.066
They don't know
the real you.

11:32.066 --> 11:34.652
Wait. That's why tonight
was such a bust.

11:34.652 --> 11:36.487
They didn't see
the real me.

11:36.487 --> 11:39.908
But we do. So now you can hang
with us for my b‐day.

11:39.908 --> 11:41.701
Don't be stupid,
stupid Matt Bradley!

11:41.701 --> 11:43.828
I'm going back to that frat
tomorrow night.

11:43.828 --> 11:45.330
But I thought those guys
rejected you.

11:45.330 --> 11:46.915
They rejected Flounder
and Bluto.

11:46.915 --> 11:48.583
I'm going back as myself.

11:48.583 --> 11:49.792
You can't, moron.

11:49.792 --> 11:51.127
And why not?

11:51.127 --> 11:52.253
Tomorrow, Beta Zeta
is having

11:52.253 --> 11:53.922
their new pledges
do a talent show.

11:53.922 --> 11:55.131
It's like "The Gong Show,"

11:55.131 --> 11:56.716
but with an irresponsible
amount of beer.

11:56.716 --> 11:57.884
They'll destroy you.

11:57.884 --> 11:59.761
Or they'll pledge me
on the spot

11:59.761 --> 12:02.347
when they hear the vocal
stylings of Big Tasty.

12:02.347 --> 12:04.515
And I know just the song.

12:04.515 --> 12:06.517
The Fat Boys?

12:06.517 --> 12:08.603
No. The <i>Frat</i> Boys.

12:08.603 --> 12:10.313
I need two of you
to fill out my crew.

12:10.313 --> 12:11.689
Barry, again,
it's Matt's birthday.

12:11.689 --> 12:13.191
We're going to hang
with him.

12:13.191 --> 12:16.653
Do you ever consider what I want
on Matt Bradley's birthday?!

12:16.653 --> 12:17.987
We hadn't.

12:17.987 --> 12:20.323
As my oldest, closest friends,

12:20.323 --> 12:23.743
you owe it to me to help me make
even newer, closer friends.

12:23.743 --> 12:24.786
We have plans.

12:25.578 --> 12:28.248
Good luck, Bar.
I hope you get what you want.

12:28.248 --> 12:31.084
I hope you get what you want
on your birthday, Matt Bradley.

12:31.084 --> 12:33.211
I know you were mocking me,
but thanks, bro.

12:33.211 --> 12:34.837
It means a lot.

12:34.837 --> 12:36.172
What's their problem?

12:36.172 --> 12:38.007
You're the one
with the problem.

12:38.007 --> 12:39.509
Crashing a party
is one thing,

12:39.509 --> 12:42.262
but crashing a fraternity
talent show is just suicide.

12:42.262 --> 12:45.098
Not if I get the real Fat Boys
to do it with me.

12:47.016 --> 12:48.351
Close enough.

12:48.351 --> 12:50.353
Thanks for the free tee.
What's this for again?

12:50.353 --> 12:53.231
Doesn't matter. You two dorks
get to go to a frat party.

12:53.231 --> 12:54.440
Isn't that enough?

12:54.440 --> 12:55.942
I hear
bikini‐clad women

12:55.942 --> 12:57.694
wrestle in kiddie pools
full of Jell‐O.

12:57.694 --> 12:59.570
‐Jell‐O!
‐Bam!

12:59.570 --> 13:01.698
Crew locked and loaded!

13:01.698 --> 13:04.367
<i>As Barry assembled two children</i>
<i>to impress grown men,</i>

13:04.367 --> 13:06.369
<i>my mom was having fun</i>
<i>with her own posse.</i>

13:06.369 --> 13:08.162
<i>First up, Tai Chi.</i>

13:08.162 --> 13:11.874
[ Slowly ]
Hiya.

13:11.874 --> 13:13.376
<i>After that,</i>
<i>they learned Spanish.</i>

13:13.376 --> 13:15.670
Instructor:
<i>Me gusta jugar al futbol.</i>

13:15.670 --> 13:18.798
All:
Me gusta jugar al futbol.

13:18.798 --> 13:20.758
Adult Adam: <i>And finally,</i>
<i>mechanical bull riding.</i>

13:20.758 --> 13:23.136
Yee‐haw!

13:23.136 --> 13:24.178
[ Laughs ]
Hang on, Beverly!

13:24.178 --> 13:25.221
Whoo! Whoo!

13:25.221 --> 13:27.265
‐Ohh!
‐Whoa!

13:27.265 --> 13:29.434
How did you do that,
Beverly?

13:29.434 --> 13:32.353
Jazzercise ‐‐
really strengthens the buttocks.

13:32.353 --> 13:35.189
You know, with strong buttocks,
anything is possible.

13:35.189 --> 13:36.774
That makes
scientific sense.

13:36.774 --> 13:39.319
Well, the butt is the face
of the back of your body.

13:39.319 --> 13:41.863
How can I make my cheeks
more rosy and plump?

13:41.863 --> 13:45.033
Easy. Tomorrow, we're going to
Booty Boogie Body Ballet.

13:45.033 --> 13:46.284
I'm in.

13:46.284 --> 13:47.243
Just wait
till Murray finds out

13:47.243 --> 13:49.287
I'm taking his friends
to butt class.

13:49.287 --> 13:50.788
Do you really think
that butt dancing

13:50.788 --> 13:51.873
is the antidote here, Bev?

13:51.873 --> 13:53.750
Oh, it's not
about butt dancing.

13:53.750 --> 13:56.002
It's about Murray
eventually realizing

13:56.002 --> 13:58.629
that he's sitting alone
at home in his chair,

13:58.629 --> 14:00.923
and that is no way
for a man to live.

14:00.923 --> 14:02.383
<i>But all my dad realized</i>

14:02.383 --> 14:03.801
<i>was that football great</i>
<i>Joe Namath</i>

14:03.801 --> 14:05.511
<i>had a cameo</i>
<i>on "Fantasy Island."</i>

14:05.511 --> 14:08.139
What?
This can't be happening.

14:08.139 --> 14:10.391
<i>And he desperately needed</i>
<i>someone to talk to about it.</i>

14:10.391 --> 14:12.894
Bill, when you get this message,
call me right away.

14:12.894 --> 14:14.479
<i>But he didn't stop there.</i>

14:14.479 --> 14:16.689
Vic, as soon as you get
this message, call me.

14:16.689 --> 14:18.524
<i>And since his pals</i>
<i>weren't around,</i>

14:18.524 --> 14:20.109
<i>he turned to anyone</i>
<i>he could find.</i>

14:20.109 --> 14:21.444
Bevy, are you home?!

14:21.444 --> 14:22.612
Adam!

14:22.612 --> 14:25.364
TV history is about to happen!

14:25.364 --> 14:27.867
Lucky?!
Where are ya, girl?

14:27.867 --> 14:31.204
<i>And that's when my dad figured</i>
<i>out why he felt so alone.</i>

14:31.204 --> 14:32.955
"Fun Times
with Murray's Friends"?

14:32.955 --> 14:35.249
Pottery class?

14:35.249 --> 14:37.001
<i>As my dad</i>
<i>was feeling left out,</i>

14:37.001 --> 14:38.878
<i>it was time for the Frat Boys</i>

14:38.878 --> 14:41.130
<i>to bust in</i>
<i>on Beta Zeta's "Gong Show."</i>

14:41.130 --> 14:43.800
That was
the last pledge, Rick.

14:43.800 --> 14:46.469
Barry: Hold on!
We got one final act

14:46.469 --> 14:49.305
for you mother‐brothers
in this animal house!

14:49.305 --> 14:50.598
‐Frat Boys!
‐Frat Boys!

14:50.598 --> 14:52.266
Frat Boys!

14:52.266 --> 14:53.726
What the hell?

14:53.726 --> 14:54.727
Should I get rid
of them?

14:54.727 --> 14:57.438
No. I actually
want to see this.

14:57.438 --> 14:59.941
[ Rapping ]
♪ We're the Frat Boys,
not the Fat Boys, ya see ♪

14:59.941 --> 15:02.735
♪ And like the Fat Boys,
we got one, two, three ♪

15:02.735 --> 15:05.321
♪ But the only cool guy
up here is me ♪

15:05.321 --> 15:07.406
♪ So please let me be
in your fraternity ♪

15:07.406 --> 15:09.867
♪ We came to party
and rock the spot ♪

15:09.867 --> 15:12.870
♪ Yeah, I'm a frat boy,
but these two are not ♪

15:12.870 --> 15:14.997
♪ Dave Kim's lame,
and my brother is short ♪

15:14.997 --> 15:17.333
♪ They're mainly up here
for moral support ♪

15:17.333 --> 15:20.044
♪ Why would I insult my crew? ♪

15:20.044 --> 15:22.547
♪ 'Cause that's just something
that frat boys do ♪

15:22.547 --> 15:24.715
♪ I'm Beta Zeta material ♪

15:24.715 --> 15:27.343
♪ I eat emcees like cereal ♪

15:27.343 --> 15:30.054
♪ Cap'n Crunch
or Frosted Flakes ♪

15:30.054 --> 15:32.306
♪ Or high‐fiber bran
to help me make ♪

15:32.306 --> 15:33.474
♪ We're the frat boys ♪

15:33.474 --> 15:34.767
♪ It's a play on words ♪

15:34.767 --> 15:37.145
♪ Like the Fat Boys,
but these two are nerds ♪

15:37.145 --> 15:38.563
♪ We're the Frat Boys ♪

15:38.563 --> 15:40.523
[ Chuckles ]

15:40.523 --> 15:41.691
What do you say?!

15:41.691 --> 15:44.443
Can I join sideways boobs
Zorro slash?

15:45.611 --> 15:48.698
[ All booing ]

15:48.698 --> 15:49.824
I'm just a boy!

15:49.824 --> 15:52.076
You're handling me
as if I'm resisting!

15:52.076 --> 15:53.995
[ Chuckles ]
Classic hazing, guys.

15:53.995 --> 15:55.163
Good stuff.

15:55.163 --> 15:57.373
I don't know
how to be more clear.

15:57.373 --> 15:59.917
You will never be
a Beta Zeta.

15:59.917 --> 16:03.379
But I'm not Flounder or Bluto.
I'm just Barry.

16:03.379 --> 16:04.589
Yeah.

16:04.589 --> 16:06.299
And that's the guy
we don't want.

16:06.299 --> 16:11.721
♪♪

16:11.721 --> 16:13.514
Bev, I'm glad
you made us come here.

16:13.514 --> 16:15.183
After this,
I'm gonna have a bowl.

16:15.183 --> 16:17.268
[ Laughing ]
It feels good in my fingers.

16:17.268 --> 16:19.103
Well, I'm glad you two
were up for it.

16:19.103 --> 16:22.064
Lord knows Murray would never
step foot in this place.

16:22.064 --> 16:24.901
Aha!
There you are!

16:24.901 --> 16:27.069
Murray, you got out
of your chair.

16:27.069 --> 16:29.363
You guys have been
prancing all over town. Why?

16:29.363 --> 16:30.740
"Why?"

16:30.740 --> 16:32.575
Because you won't!
Vic: Oh, no.

16:32.575 --> 16:33.868
I was trying
to slow this thing down,

16:33.868 --> 16:35.077
but I spun it up.

16:35.077 --> 16:36.370
Bill, I could use
your hands.

16:36.370 --> 16:38.039
‐I got you, buddy.
‐Aah.

16:38.039 --> 16:40.416
Is this because of all
those dumb activities
you wanted me to do?

16:40.416 --> 16:42.043
Yes.
Aah!

16:42.043 --> 16:43.502
You know what, Murray?

16:43.502 --> 16:45.296
I always assumed that
when the kids left home,

16:45.296 --> 16:47.798
I'd at least have you
to spend my days with.

16:47.798 --> 16:48.633
Boy, was I wrong.

16:48.633 --> 16:50.051
Ahh.

16:50.051 --> 16:52.720
So I like to sit.
What's the big deal?

16:52.720 --> 16:54.138
The big deal is,

16:54.138 --> 16:55.765
the only reason
you came down here

16:55.765 --> 16:57.850
is because your friends
weren't around.

16:57.850 --> 16:59.560
You got out of your chair
for <i>them,</i>

16:59.560 --> 17:02.438
but for me, you were happy
to just sit there.

17:02.438 --> 17:05.191
♪♪

17:05.191 --> 17:07.276
Ah, ah.
There we go.

17:09.737 --> 17:12.907
<i>After Beta Zeta rejected Barry</i>
<i>for being himself,</i>

17:12.907 --> 17:14.450
<i>he had no choice but to shed</i>
<i>his dream of frat‐boy life.</i>

17:14.450 --> 17:15.660
What are you doing?

17:15.660 --> 17:17.203
Tossing out all the things
I'd been saving

17:17.203 --> 17:19.163
for the day I finally joined
a fraternity.

17:19.163 --> 17:20.873
Goodbye, pledge paddle.

17:20.873 --> 17:22.917
You will never redden
the tushies of my friends.

17:22.917 --> 17:24.001
That's Mom's cheese board.

17:24.001 --> 17:25.586
Goodbye, togas,

17:25.586 --> 17:27.004
the preferred apparel
of Greek gods and ghosts.

17:27.004 --> 17:28.506
Those are my bed sheets.

17:28.506 --> 17:30.508
Here. Maybe you can find
a better home for them.

17:30.508 --> 17:32.301
I'll probably just continue
to use them as sheets.

17:32.301 --> 17:33.427
Goodbye, beer funnel.

17:33.427 --> 17:34.887
That's a traffic cone.

17:34.887 --> 17:38.099
Listen, Barry, you're <i>so</i> much
better without those guys.

17:38.099 --> 17:39.475
No, I'm not.

17:39.475 --> 17:42.061
One of the reasons
why I love "Animal House"

17:42.061 --> 17:45.356
was the idea that you could go
from being a loser one minute

17:45.356 --> 17:47.108
to having 50 best friends
the next.

17:47.108 --> 17:49.026
You don't need
a fraternity to do that.

17:49.026 --> 17:50.987
Well, it hasn't happened
in this dorm

17:50.987 --> 17:53.072
or anywhere else
at this college.

17:53.072 --> 17:55.908
Maybe Rick is right ‐‐
I'm not good enough.

17:55.908 --> 17:57.451
Don't you get it?

17:57.451 --> 17:59.412
You already belong
to an amazing fraternity,

17:59.412 --> 18:00.955
with true friends
who love you.

18:00.955 --> 18:01.956
Who?

18:01.956 --> 18:02.999
The JTP.

18:04.584 --> 18:06.544
And they're struggling
as much as you are.

18:06.544 --> 18:07.795
[ Sighs ]

18:07.795 --> 18:09.255
I was such a jerk
to them...

18:09.255 --> 18:10.673
Such a jerk.

18:10.673 --> 18:13.009
But the great thing
about that is,

18:13.009 --> 18:15.177
a brother
always forgives.

18:15.177 --> 18:16.512
Matt Bradley's birthday!

18:16.512 --> 18:17.597
Go.

18:17.597 --> 18:19.515
[ Sighs ]

18:19.515 --> 18:21.058
Thanks, Erica.

18:21.058 --> 18:23.311
<i>While Barry got emotional</i>
<i>about his old friends,</i>

18:23.311 --> 18:25.521
<i>our dad decided it was time</i>
<i>to get physical.</i>

18:25.521 --> 18:26.689
I'm a‐ready.

18:26.689 --> 18:28.316
What am I looking at?

18:28.316 --> 18:31.861
I thought the two of us
could do the Jazzercise.

18:31.861 --> 18:33.404
What?

18:33.404 --> 18:35.448
You know, the thing
with the jumping around

18:35.448 --> 18:37.325
and the crappy music
that you love so much.

18:38.534 --> 18:39.827
[ Up‐tempo music plays ]

18:39.827 --> 18:41.746
I'm doing it up.

18:41.746 --> 18:42.705
Jazzercising.

18:42.705 --> 18:44.165
Jazzercising.

18:44.165 --> 18:46.626
♪♪

18:46.626 --> 18:48.753
Can't stop Jazzercising.

18:48.753 --> 18:50.171
I can't do it!
[ Music stops ]

18:50.171 --> 18:52.506
Murray, we've got to
figure this out.

18:52.506 --> 18:55.009
The rest of our lives is coming
sooner than you think.

18:55.009 --> 18:57.053
Yeah. I know.

18:57.053 --> 18:59.722
I was, uh, walking
around the house,

18:59.722 --> 19:03.684
and I couldn't find anybody
and I, uh...

19:03.684 --> 19:04.560
Felt alone?

19:04.560 --> 19:06.187
Yeah, maybe.

19:06.187 --> 19:08.022
Y‐You know the words
better than me.

19:08.022 --> 19:10.232
And you thought maybe
it would be nice

19:10.232 --> 19:12.818
to be surrounded by people
who love you.

19:12.818 --> 19:14.487
Sure. Uh, yeah.

19:14.487 --> 19:18.032
And you realized
that without those people,

19:18.032 --> 19:20.117
the future
might not be so great.

19:20.117 --> 19:23.120
It's so hard for me to get
excited about doing stuff,

19:23.120 --> 19:25.539
and there's only three things
I like ‐‐

19:25.539 --> 19:30.044
sitting, watching sports,
and you.

19:30.044 --> 19:32.296
♪ You might think I'm crazy ♪

19:32.296 --> 19:34.507
I can work with that.

19:34.507 --> 19:37.301
<i>That night, my dad learned</i>
<i>that being together</i>

19:37.301 --> 19:39.470
<i>was the only thing my mom</i>
<i>ever really wanted.</i>

19:39.470 --> 19:41.847
<i>It's what everyone wants ‐‐</i>

19:41.847 --> 19:44.684
<i>someone who will be there</i>
<i>no matter what.</i>

19:44.684 --> 19:46.477
Aww. Thanks, guys.

19:46.477 --> 19:48.104
[ Blows ]

19:48.104 --> 19:49.355
All: JTP!

19:49.355 --> 19:51.691
JTP!

19:51.691 --> 19:53.442
Hey. Why aren't you
hanging out

19:53.442 --> 19:55.361
with your new
fraternity brothers?

19:55.361 --> 19:57.697
'Cause I already
have brothers,

19:57.697 --> 20:00.491
and they make up the greatest
fraternity known to man ‐‐

20:00.491 --> 20:02.410
JTP.

20:02.410 --> 20:04.870
I'm sorry I wasn't there
for you guys.

20:04.870 --> 20:07.331
Doesn't matter
'cause you're here now.

20:07.331 --> 20:08.958
JTP.

20:08.958 --> 20:10.251
All: JTP!

20:10.251 --> 20:11.794
Now let's give stupid,
sweet Matt Bradley

20:11.794 --> 20:13.254
his birthday spanking.

20:13.254 --> 20:15.798
<i>In the end, it's not always</i>
<i>about what you do.</i>

20:15.798 --> 20:18.801
<i>It's who you do it with</i>
<i>that matters most.</i>

20:18.801 --> 20:20.177
Ta‐da.

20:20.177 --> 20:22.221
Oh! That is perfect!

20:22.221 --> 20:23.681
Let me see yours.

20:23.681 --> 20:27.643
I made a calendar to show all
